1
00:00:00,840 --> 00:00:03,000
<i>At the wedding,</i>

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:07,050
- <i>the one who drugged my wife...</i>
- Sayaka!

3
00:00:07,050 --> 00:00:08,240
You held ill will towards Sayaka.

4
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:10,450
Ill will?

5
00:00:10,450 --> 00:00:11,950
Ridiculous.

6
00:00:11,950 --> 00:00:15,970
- The culprit is...
- Yeah.

7
00:00:15,970 --> 00:00:19,920
<i>It was her own mother, Kaori Wakamatsu.</i>

8
00:00:26,340 --> 00:00:30,400
What will you do now?

9
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:36,440
Will you report her actions to the police?

10
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:40,440
If only I could.

11
00:00:43,950 --> 00:00:47,050
She could very well be the culprit.

12
00:00:49,480 --> 00:00:53,680
She is the culprit.

13
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:56,730
And she's absolutely despicable as a mother.

14
00:00:58,330 --> 00:01:04,130
But she's still Sayaka's mother.

15
00:01:07,050 --> 00:01:12,650
Sayaka doesn't know she was drugged.

16
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:17,780
If I told her about her mother's actions...

17
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,250
She would be devastated.

18
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:28,070
We found no evidence against Sayaka's mother.

19
00:01:30,670 --> 00:01:35,440
It's best we keep this on the down-low.

20
00:01:36,660 --> 00:01:40,010
You make a point.

21
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:48,360
I'm sorry. I said we ought to be cautious,

22
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:51,550
yet I went and ran my mouth back there.

23
00:01:51,550 --> 00:01:54,000
Don't let it bother you.

24
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:59,740
I also have a bucket load of complaints
I could make

25
00:01:59,740 --> 00:02:01,600
about that mother of hers.

26
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,310
But I made you take my side.

27
00:02:05,770 --> 00:02:12,810
You defended my education, and upbringing.

28
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:22,250
I was honestly a bit surprised.

29
00:02:27,410 --> 00:02:29,210
Still, I appreciated the support.

30
00:02:30,290 --> 00:02:33,400
Thank you.

31
00:02:37,090 --> 00:02:41,950
I was only stating the obvious.

32
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:51,690
See you around.

33
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:53,150
See you.

34
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:06,630
Hayashida!

35
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:11,820
I forgot I still had Sayaka's albums.
[2019 High School Album]

36
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:21,760
Since we have them,
could you make that slideshow after all?

37
00:03:25,290 --> 00:03:28,200
Sure thing.

38
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:32,920
Thanks.

39
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:37,350
We also need a photographer on the day of...

40
00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:40,690
I already planned to be there.

41
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:43,970
Thank you.

42
00:03:43,970 --> 00:03:46,760
Then I'll see you at the ceremony.

43
00:03:51,330 --> 00:03:53,220
Sakuraba, wait!

44
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:00,020
Look.

45
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:09,430
You're the only reason
I found out as much as I did.

46
00:04:11,740 --> 00:04:14,650
Seriously, thanks for everything.

47
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:20,140
I'm glad I could help.

48
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,140
I suppose we call it here?

49
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:37,590
Yeah.

50
00:04:43,490 --> 00:04:49,720
<i>This was how our case came to a close.</i>

51
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:53,420
<i>From now on...</i>

52
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:57,860
<i>I vow to live solely for Sayaka's sake.</i>

53
00:05:06,010 --> 00:05:08,730
Where should we go today?

54
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:13,010
I'm fine going anywhere,
so long as you're with me.

55
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,450
Sayaka, here. It's going to be cold today.

56
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:18,060
Thanks.

57
00:05:25,150 --> 00:05:27,610
<i>This weekend is all about the two of us.</i>

58
00:05:28,550 --> 00:05:30,680
<i>I'm a happy man.</i>

59
00:05:33,220 --> 00:05:35,430
So cute.

60
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:43,050
What's your pick? Vanilla, or chocolate?

61
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:45,620
[Winter Ice Pancake - Vanilla or Chocolate]
That's a hard question.

62
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:50,160
<i>Then let's just get both, and share them.</i>

63
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,220
We spent a lot of money today.

64
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:06,990
Everything is for the ceremony.

65
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:13,470
Should I go find a job soon?

66
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:17,080
You don't need to work, Sayaka.

67
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:20,240
But I've recovered already.

68
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,380
No pushing yourself, alright?

69
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:24,910
It's okay to take it easy at home.

70
00:06:24,910 --> 00:06:27,000
Especially with the ceremony coming up.

71
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:30,060
You're right.

72
00:06:30,060 --> 00:06:33,460
We still have tons we need to prepare.

73
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:39,560
We'll need to send out invitations soon.

74
00:06:41,550 --> 00:06:44,920
Chie and Airi both want to come again.

75
00:06:47,090 --> 00:06:50,920
What about you, Kazu?

76
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:54,840
Will you be inviting the same people
as last time?

77
00:06:56,310 --> 00:06:57,630
<i>Sayaka and I</i>

78
00:06:57,630 --> 00:07:01,630
were only friends with benefits.

79
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:05,240
<i>Don't let the past affect you.</i>

80
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,460
<i>Move on.</i>

81
00:07:07,460 --> 00:07:09,490
<i>That's what you decided, right?</i>

82
00:07:11,950 --> 00:07:15,840
Yeah. I'll be inviting the same folks.

83
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:17,480
I see.

84
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:20,860
Let's order that blue champagne, too.

85
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:25,130
I want that drink
to remain a special memory for us.

86
00:07:25,130 --> 00:07:26,140
Yeah.

87
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:31,480
And don't feel pressured
to perform the violin this time.

88
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:37,090
This is our ceremony.

89
00:07:38,810 --> 00:07:41,530
No, it's your ceremony.

90
00:07:41,530 --> 00:07:45,580
So let's make it a memorable one, yeah?

91
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:03,180
What's for dinner, Sayaka?

92
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:05,240
Curry.

93
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,990
- What?
- Nothing.

94
00:08:21,010 --> 00:08:22,920
I vow to you, Sayaka.

95
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:27,810
I will continue loving you,

96
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:33,020
both now and forevermore.

97
00:08:39,410 --> 00:08:43,850
<i>Thank you, Kazu.</i>

98
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:01,460
[Town Hall]

99
00:09:05,310 --> 00:09:11,650
<i>I'll dedicate my life to Sayaka,
no matter what comes our way.</i>

100
00:09:15,910 --> 00:09:19,550
[Recommended Wedding Songs]

101
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:26,850
<i>I'll protect her from evil,
no matter the cost.</i>

102
00:09:33,210 --> 00:09:34,140
What?

103
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:36,930
It's leaking out, you know.

104
00:09:36,930 --> 00:09:39,180
My bad. Was the music loud?

105
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:44,020
I was referring to your obvious good mood.

106
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:45,980
Did something happen?

107
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:52,190
You seem to be in high spirits.

108
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:53,860
I'm not telling a gossip like you.

109
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:56,790
That rumor wasn't from me, okay?

110
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:58,160
Hey, lunch looks good.

111
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:00,220
- Pretty please? Can I have a bite?
- Don't touch it.

112
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:02,960
- Let me... Ow!
- Back off.

113
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,430
[2019 High School Album]

114
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:21,010
[SS-studio]

115
00:10:21,010 --> 00:10:25,110
Welcome back. We've been waiting for you.

116
00:10:25,110 --> 00:10:26,560
Thank you.

117
00:10:32,050 --> 00:10:34,070
I'm home.

118
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:42,060
Sayaka?

119
00:10:56,220 --> 00:10:58,850
Thanks for watching her for me.

120
00:10:58,850 --> 00:11:00,860
You're always such great help.

121
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:06,340
Are these your graduation albums?

122
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:08,610
No, those are from a client.

123
00:11:08,610 --> 00:11:10,940
Are these... Hold her for me.

124
00:11:11,540 --> 00:11:15,920
Asahi Central Middle School.
Are these Sayaka's?

125
00:11:18,090 --> 00:11:22,210
Kazuomi! Thank you for the other day.

126
00:11:23,570 --> 00:11:27,980
You treated me to lunch, remember?

127
00:11:29,070 --> 00:11:33,030
Now, play this section for me again.

128
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:34,510
Yes, Mother.

129
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:44,270
No, you must play that in tempo.

130
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:49,040
This is a simple passage.
You ought to do better.

131
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:51,110
I'm sorry.

132
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:53,010
Goodness, what a disaster.

133
00:11:53,010 --> 00:11:55,200
She hasn't practiced at all

134
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:59,890
since I handed you that sheet music, Kazuomi.

135
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:05,070
That wouldn't be Sayaka's fault, Mother.

136
00:12:05,070 --> 00:12:05,910
What?

137
00:12:05,910 --> 00:12:10,910
I never handed her your sheet music.

138
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:16,060
Sayaka won't be performing the violin
at our upcoming ceremony.

139
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:18,490
Didn't they already have a wedding?

140
00:12:18,490 --> 00:12:23,420
Yes, but they've decided
to redo their ceremony.

141
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:25,830
Redo... Why?

142
00:12:25,830 --> 00:12:28,960
Great question...

143
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:33,950
In any case, that's what the albums are for.

144
00:12:35,850 --> 00:12:41,000
If I were you, I wouldn't use these photos.

145
00:12:42,090 --> 00:12:43,600
What?

146
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:47,680
Middle school was a low point for Sayaka.

147
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,840
You aren't thinking
in Sayaka's best interests.

148
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:52,970
Please don't force her to perform.

149
00:12:52,970 --> 00:12:55,630
Force her?

150
00:13:00,010 --> 00:13:02,850
Gosh, how revolting.

151
00:13:06,390 --> 00:13:11,150
Sayaka was caught shoplifting.
She was a real bully, too.

152
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:12,880
I don't believe it...

153
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:14,580
It's the truth, I tell you.

154
00:13:14,580 --> 00:13:18,810
I couldn't talk about it
with her husband here,

155
00:13:18,810 --> 00:13:22,110
but my nephew told me all about her.

156
00:13:22,110 --> 00:13:26,910
The shoplifting in particular happened

157
00:13:26,910 --> 00:13:30,250
in their first year of middle school.

158
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:32,900
The police caught her?

159
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:39,310
That's right.
But the incident ended just like that.

160
00:13:39,310 --> 00:13:43,500
I'm sure Kaori snuffed out all the rumors.

161
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:46,140
"Revolting"?

162
00:13:46,140 --> 00:13:48,410
Sayaka is your daughter.

163
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:51,710
Can you believe her?
She uses her charm to cling to men,

164
00:13:51,710 --> 00:13:54,280
and seduces all of those who surround her.

165
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,410
How absolutely shameful.

166
00:13:55,410 --> 00:13:57,720
Sayaka is seducing no one.

167
00:13:57,720 --> 00:14:02,830
And she is my wife.
Of course she can cling to me.

168
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:10,860
Girls are cruel bullies, you know?

169
00:14:10,860 --> 00:14:13,400
My nephew actually witnessed
an incident firsthand.

170
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:16,390
Sayaka and her friends
called a girl out back,

171
00:14:16,390 --> 00:14:19,070
and pushed her around
while calling her names.

172
00:14:19,070 --> 00:14:21,890
They also threw that girl's bag into a lake,

173
00:14:21,890 --> 00:14:28,440
and laughed as she got her things back.

174
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:36,060
Worst of all, Sayaka and her group
would film the poor girl.

175
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:41,480
Then that picture...

176
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,790
[Unhappiest wishes to you, Red Riding Hood]

177
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:52,060
I'll see you both at the ceremony.

178
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:12,140
It's going to be okay.

179
00:15:13,710 --> 00:15:15,640
Kazu...

180
00:15:24,940 --> 00:15:27,520
Please don't come to our ceremony.

181
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:29,030
What?

182
00:15:29,030 --> 00:15:33,980
We had no intent on inviting you, Mother.

183
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:39,030
Please don't hurt Sayaka any further.

184
00:15:39,670 --> 00:15:43,150
I hurt her?

185
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:44,610
Yes.

186
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:48,300
So please, leave Sayaka alone.

187
00:15:53,810 --> 00:15:55,810
I see.

188
00:15:55,810 --> 00:15:57,440
Fine, if you so insist.

189
00:16:26,340 --> 00:16:29,220
<i>Tricked by the Big Bad Wolf,</i>

190
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:32,350
<i>Little Red Riding Hood was swallowed whole.</i>

191
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:40,860
<i>After being saved by the hunter,</i>

192
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:46,990
<i>Red Riding Hood kills the sleeping wolf,
by stuffing it full of stones.</i>

193
00:16:52,540 --> 00:16:54,550
What's up, Sachiko?

194
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:02,750
[SS-studio]

195
00:17:04,650 --> 00:17:06,030
Hey there.

196
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,990
Sachiko!

197
00:17:13,990 --> 00:17:16,630
Were you waiting for me?

198
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:29,990
This is a nostalgic shot.

199
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,860
I've never seen this picture before.

200
00:17:37,770 --> 00:17:39,540
What a throwback.

201
00:17:39,540 --> 00:17:43,920
That's a shot your friend sent me.

202
00:17:46,030 --> 00:17:47,980
Thanks.

203
00:17:48,870 --> 00:17:51,480
Wow, this looks delicious.

204
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,730
Thanks for the meal.

205
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,500
This is great.

206
00:18:06,690 --> 00:18:12,470
Hayashida. We need to talk about Sayaka.

207
00:18:17,260 --> 00:18:19,310
What? Of course not.

208
00:18:19,310 --> 00:18:21,950
For now, we can set the shoplifting aside.

209
00:18:21,950 --> 00:18:27,160
But one thing is certain. Sayaka was a bully.

210
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:31,480
It seems her actions were no laughing matter.

211
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:33,850
She did some truly heinous things.

212
00:18:39,030 --> 00:18:40,650
Now hold on.

213
00:18:41,460 --> 00:18:43,590
This is Sayaka we're talking about.

214
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:47,200
The meek Sayaka, who's always apologizing.

215
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:50,610
The Sayaka who struggles to speak her mind.

216
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:54,410
She was more likely to be the victim.

217
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:58,010
Definitely not the bully herself.

218
00:19:01,060 --> 00:19:03,430
And if she were involved,

219
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:08,620
she was likely forced into it.

220
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:13,110
I can practically imagine her troubled face.

221
00:19:16,450 --> 00:19:18,810
You agree with me, don't you?

222
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:22,590
Hayashida...

223
00:19:24,550 --> 00:19:26,580
What?

224
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:36,000
Point is, I believe none of it.

225
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,180
Thanks for the meal.

226
00:19:42,110 --> 00:19:43,870
I'll be heading out.

227
00:19:58,460 --> 00:20:01,520
We already found the culprit.

228
00:20:02,170 --> 00:20:07,470
So why do I feel like
we're missing something?

229
00:20:13,260 --> 00:20:15,150
[Class 3-C]

230
00:20:16,390 --> 00:20:21,000
<i>There's a continuation to the tale
of Little Red Riding Hood.</i>

231
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,060
[Shining Days]

232
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:26,190
<i>With her previous experience under her belt,</i>
[Class A]

233
00:20:26,190 --> 00:20:32,240
<i>Little Red Riding Hood turns the tides,</i>

234
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:34,290
<i>and kills any wolves who cross her path.</i>

235
00:20:34,290 --> 00:20:37,030
<i>Sayaka and her friends
called a girl out back,</i>

236
00:20:37,030 --> 00:20:39,520
<i>and pushed her around
while calling her names.</i>

237
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:47,480
<i>Worst of all, they would film the poor girl.</i>

238
00:20:59,380 --> 00:21:03,190
I'm seeing the bigger picture now.

239
00:21:03,190 --> 00:21:06,390
<i>In other words, Little Red Riding Hood...</i>

240
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:07,710
Want a taste?

241
00:21:07,710 --> 00:21:09,250
Sure.

242
00:21:11,610 --> 00:21:16,830
<i>Was never a weak, innocent little girl.</i>

243
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,300
[Guests]

244
00:21:26,290 --> 00:21:31,330
[Friend of the Groom - Akira Mori]

245
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:46,030
Hello there.

246
00:21:48,190 --> 00:21:50,230
I apologize for the sudden appointment.

247
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:56,830
I wished to confirm one thing
about Hayashida's wedding.

248
00:21:56,830 --> 00:21:59,550
Confirm...

249
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,840
Oh, is this about tomorrow's ceremony?

250
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:07,590
No, I'd like to ask about the first ceremony.

251
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:22,730
Sayaka.

252
00:22:38,010 --> 00:22:39,900
Come in.

253
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:42,460
Mr. Hayashida, we've got a problem.
